---
title: 'Student assistant position: Python developer in the PORQUE project'
---

We are looking for a student research assistant to help us with the development of a knowledge graphs based multilingual question answering system. We expect the student to have foundational understanding of the following topics:
- Knowledge Graphs
- Machine learning
- Natural language processing

Also, we expect the student to have experience in working with Python libraries such as Numpy, PyTorch, Hugging Face etc.

As per your requirement, we can offer a work contract ranging from 9 to 19 hours/week. If you are interested, please send an email to nikit.srivastava@upb.de with your CV and motivation letter.

For further information please contact [Nikit Srivastava](/NikitSrivastava).
